Falmer Stadium, known for sponsorship purposes as the American Express Community Stadium, or colloquially as the Amex, is a football stadium in the village of Falmer, near Brighton and Hove, Sussex, that serves as the home of Brighton and Hove Albion F.C. The first competitive game played at the stadium was the 2010 to 11 season final of the Sussex Senior Cup between Brighton and Eastbourne Borough on 16 July 2011. 
